snippet.textDisplay: Honestly, i agree with your decision. Even tho it breaks my heart to see Shadow go, i understand ❤💕4 years ago, with my parents, we brought our dog(Doupy) to visit our family. My grandma's dog(a jack russel named Touche, he was very old 14yo) and mine (a tiny springer spaniel) really got along, they were really good friends and cared a lot about each other. But sadly my uncle's dog(Stitch) got really jealous of my dog's arrival i think. He was much more heavier and one night, when we were at a festival, he attacked my grandma's dog and mine. He almost killed them both. When i came home i ran to the door because i was cold and i literally found my grandma's dog half dead covered in blood, lying down on the floor in front of the entrance. It traumatized me. Hopefully my dog only had a few cuts, but he didnt loose as much blood as my grandma's dog did. They both survived but my grandma's dog died of old age 3years ago. I'll never forget any of this. It really shocked me, and i wish to never live that again. A dangerous fight between dogs you love really breaks your heart, no matter the consequences. I wish you good luck. Im sorry for what you had to go trough ❤💖💕

snippet.textDisplay:
My ex’s dog has severe food aggression and both she (dog) and my dog are over 60 lbs. We had someone watch them when we went outbid town once, told them specific instructions on how to feed them, but they didn’t listen and fed them right next to each other.

We came home to blood all over the walls and the dogs. And urine everywhere. They’d already gone to the vet — one had an inch deep hash on their tongue. It was horrifying and still really messes with me when I think about it. When we broke up and moved to separate places, it was the first time I felt like I could relax for the first time in a long time. I totally understand why you’re doing what you’re doing. It’s never easy — they’re our kids. It shows maturity and love when you’re able to make a decision like this.
